# Overview: DGP $\times$ Method Heatmaps {#sec-overview}

The heatmaps below show the **median** of each metric across all 600 runs per cell
(100 reps $\times$ 2 severity $\times$ 3 noise), giving a quick orientation.
Color encodes the **rank** within each DGP (row): yellow = best (rank 1),
purple = worst (rank 5). Numeric labels show the actual median values.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
make_heatmap(dt, "warp_mise", "Warp MISE (median, all conditions)")
```

