# Registration Diagnostics {#sec-diag}

## Over/under-registration (Q4) {#sec-q4}

*Question: Do methods systematically over-register or under-register?*

The **registration ratio** measures how much the estimated warp deviates from
the identity relative to the true warp:
$$R_i = \frac{\|\hat{h}_i - \mathrm{id}\|^2}{\|h_i - \mathrm{id}\|^2}$$
where $\|\cdot\|^2 = \int_0^1 (\cdot)^2\,dt$.
Values $R < 1$ indicate under-registration (estimated warp closer to identity
than truth); $R > 1$ indicates over-registration (warped too much).
We report the median $R$ across curves within each run.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
make_reg_ratio_plot(dt)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![Registration ratio by method, stratified by warp type (rows) and severity × noise (columns). Each dot = one DGP (median over 100 reps); crossbar = median across DGPs. Dashed line at 1 = perfectly calibrated.](sim-report-main_files/figure-html/q4-reg-ratio-1.png){width=960}
:::
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
