The **warp slope ratio** measures how much "wiggliness" the estimated warp has
relative to the truth:
$$S_i = \frac{\max \hat{h}_i'(t) - \min \hat{h}_i'(t)}{\max h_i'(t) - \min h_i'(t)}$$
Values $S > 1$ mean the estimated warp is too wiggly; $S < 1$ means too smooth.
This diagnostic is only meaningful for non-affine warps (affine warps have
constant derivative, making the denominator uninformative).


::: {.cell}

